name: Warung Makan Jaya Asih
address: Sembung, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Really affordable family restaurant to eat at on the way north. Right next to a padi field, the view was relaxing and the food was tasty and acceptable.
review 2: If you are on the way, highly recommend to try this local family restaurant. Very delicious food, local prices and Balinese hospitality. What you see in pictures cost 75k IDR on 2024 April
review 3:
As authentic as it can get!

We stopped here on our way back to Ubud. Immediately were greeted in the wamr Balinese manner by the family.

Placed our order of Nasi goreng and Mahi mahi fish meal with orange and pineapple fresh juice. All of it was delicious.

Then even let my curious husband loom around the kitchen and offered him some Durian when he mentioned that he loves it.

Place was clean, food was hygienic and people were very sweet.

We also got to play with their kitten while we waited for the food.
We couldn't enjoy the view as we went there at night but you can find many beautifully take pics of the paddy fields in other reviews.

Devi and family: thank you for your hospitality and taking care of us with the scrumptious meal. We will visit again!
review 4: This place was amazing. We loved the food and the family was very nice. Also the view is spectacular and an added bonus.
review 5: Good music, delicious food, friendly atmosphere. Thank you! we'll be back again ‚ù§Ô∏è
